cdevariables.name: Alzheimer Broad Category
cdevariables.description: There will be two broad categories taken into account. Alzheimer s disease (AD) in which the diagnostic is 100% certain and <Other> comprising the rest of Alzheimer s related categories. The <Other> category refers to Alzheime s related diagnosis which origin can be traced to other pathology eg. vascular. In this category MCI diagnosis can also be found. In summary  all Alzheimer s related diagnosis that are not pure.

cdevariables.name: MMSE Total scores
cdevariables.description: The Mini Mental State Examination (MMSE) or Folstein test is a 30-point questionnaire that is used extensively in clinical and research settings to measure cognitive impairment. It is commonly used to screen for dementia.

cdevariables.name: pTau status
cdevariables.description: the phosphorylated tau proteins level is pathological if it is superior to 60

cdevariables.name: MoCA Total
cdevariables.description: The Montreal Cognitive Assessment (MoCA) was designed as a rapid screening instrument for mild cognitive dysfunction. It assesses different cognitive domains: attention and concentration  executive functions  memory  language  visuoconstructional skills  conceptual thinking  calculations  and orientation. MoCA Total Scores refer to the final count obtained by patients after the complete test is performed.

cdevariables.name: UPDRS HY
cdevariables.description: The Hoehn and Yahr scale (HY) is a widely used clinical rating scale  which defines broad categories of motor function in Parkinson\u2019s disease (PD). It captures typical patterns of progressive motor impairment.

cdevariables.name: UPDRS Total
cdevariables.description: The unified Parkinson s disease rating scale (UPDRS) is used to follow the longitudinal course of Parkinson s disease. The UPD rating scale is the most commonly used scale in the clinical study of Parkinson s disease.

cdevariables.name: Handedness

cdevariables.name: ApoE4
cdevariables.description: Apolipoprotein E (APOE) e4 allele: is the strongest risk factor for Late Onset Alzheimer Disease (LOAD). At least one copy of APOE-e4

cdevariables.name: Dataset
cdevariables.description: Variable used to differentiate datasets

cdevariables.name: Level of amyloid beta 1-42 peptides in cerebrospinal fluid
cdevariables.description: A\u03b2 is the main component of amyloid plaques (extracellular deposits found in the brains of patients with Alzheimer’s disease). Similar plaques appear in some variants of Lewy body dementia and in inclusion body myositis (a muscle disease), while A\u03b2 can also form the aggregates that coat cerebral blood vessels in cerebral amyloid angiopathy. The plaques are composed of a tangle of regularly ordered fibrillar aggregates called amyloid fibers, a protein fold shared by other peptides such as the prions associated with protein misfolding diseases.

cdevariables.name: amyloid 42 status
cdevariables.description: the amyloid 42 level is pathological if the level is inferior to 700

cdevariables.name: Level of amyloid beta 1-40 peptides in cerebrospinal fluid
cdevariables.description: A\u03b2 is the main component of amyloid plaques (extracellular deposits found in the brains of patients with Alzheimer's disease). Similar plaques appear in some variants of Lewy body dementia and in inclusion body myositis (a muscle disease), while A\u03b2 can also form the aggregates that coat cerebral blood vessels in cerebral amyloid angiopathy. The plaques are composed of a tangle of regularly ordered fibrillar aggregates called amyloid fibers, a protein fold shared by other peptides such as the prions associated with protein misfolding diseases.

cdevariables.name: Total level of tau proteins in cerebrospinal fluid
cdevariables.description: Tau proteins (or \u03c4 proteins) are proteins that stabilize microtubules. They are abundant in neurons of the central nervous system and are less common elsewhere, but are also expressed at very low levels in CNS astrocytes and oligodendrocytes. Pathologies and dementias of the nervous system such as Alzheimer’s disease and Parkinson’s disease are associated with tau proteins that have become defective and no longer stabilize microtubules properly.

cdevariables.name: Level of phosphorylated tau proteins in cerebrospinal fluid
cdevariables.description: Hyperphosphorylation of the tau protein (tau inclusions, pTau) can result in the self-assembly of tangles of paired helical filaments and straight filaments, which are involved in the pathogenesis of Alzheimer's disease, frontotemporal dementia, and other tauopathies.

cdevariables.name: Resection procedure date
cdevariables.description: The resection date is calculated according to the SEEG date.

cdevariables.name: Age
cdevariables.description: Value in months for participant/subject's age, calculated as elapsed time since the birth of the participant/subject.

cdevariables.name: Sex
cdevariables.description: Birth sex assigned type : male, female.

cdevariables.name: Febrile convulsions indicator
cdevariables.description: Indicate if the patient had febrile convulsions.

cdevariables.name: Neonatal disorder indicator
cdevariables.description: Indicate if the patient had neonatal disorder.

cdevariables.name: CNS infection indicator
cdevariables.description: Indicate if the patient had CNS infection.

cdevariables.name: Additional conditions indicator
cdevariables.description: Indicate the presence of one or more additional conditions co-occuring.

cdevariables.name: Hand preference type
cdevariables.description: Choose the hand which the participant/subject uses predominantly, not necessarily the hand the participant/subject writes with exclusively

cdevariables.name: physical exam indicator
cdevariables.description: Indicate if a clinical exam has been done.

cdevariables.name: Type of Epilepsy
cdevariables.description: Type of epilepsy diagnosed after the SEEG

cdevariables.name: Duration at the first SEEG.
cdevariables.description: The epilepsy duration at the first SEEG.

cdevariables.name: Post resection MRI Imaging date
cdevariables.description: MRI date after the surgery and it’s calculated according to the SEEG date

cdevariables.name: Participant Age when first seizure occurred
cdevariables.description: Value in months for participant/subject's age, calculated as elapsed time since the date of birth of the participant/subject at the date of first seizure experienced; A seizure, formally known as an epileptic seizure, is a period of symptoms due to abnormally excessive or synchronous neuronal activity in the brain.

cdevariables.name: Epilepsy syndrome history
cdevariables.values: {"N","No history"},{"U","Unknown"},{"Y_febrile_convulsions","Yes - Febrile convulsions"},{"Y_TBI","Yes - TBI"},{"Y_CNS_infection","Yes - CNS infection"},{"Y_neonatal_disorder","Yes - Neonatal disorder"},{"Y_vascular","Yes – Vascular"}
cdevariables.description: Epilepsy syndrome observed on the participant/subject in the past

cdevariables.name: Seizure type during SEEG
cdevariables.description: Indicate the type of seizure occurring during the seeg.

cdevariables.name: Seizure during SEEG freq.
cdevariables.description: Indicate the frequency of the seizures occurrence during the SEEG.

cdevariables.name: Medication concomitant CCEP
cdevariables.description: Antiepileptic medication intake during CCEP. n/a means the entry was left empty.

cdevariables.name: Medication concomitant CCEP – Other
cdevariables.description: Other medication intake during CCEP. n/a means the entry was left empty.

cdevariables.name: Antiepileptic treatment
cdevariables.description: Antiepileptic treatment taken by the patient

cdevariables.name: Anatomical lesion observed
cdevariables.description: Anatomical lesion observed on the participant/subject

cdevariables.name: Anatomical lesion classification
cdevariables.description: Anatomical lesion observed classification

cdevariables.name: Surgery post-operative seizure indicator
cdevariables.description: Indicate if the patient had seizure after the surgery and give the frequency.

cdevariables.name: Engel score
cdevariables.values: {"U","Unknown"},{"I","Free of disabling seizures"},{"II","Rare disabling seizures"},{"III","Worthwile improvement"},{"IV","No worthwile improvement"}
cdevariables.description: Give the score at the engel test.

cdevariables.name: SEEG Date
cdevariables.description: The SEEG date is considered as the reference. An anomysed value is given.

cdevariables.name: Coagulation date
cdevariables.description: The coagulation date is calculated according to the SEEG date.
